Date: 17/5/1864
Source: Wellington Independent
Author:
Vol / Page: 2
Edition:
Quote: The fanaticism which believes in the utterance of the word "hau" in a yelping tone, as a powerful means of procuring the favor of Heaven and bringing death on the settlers, is not likely to meet with much that will strengthen it, and after awhile [sic] these "Pai Marire" will be as little heard of as the Lizard Hunters of a year or two ago.
